.TH TCP_SYN_STOP 8 "__DATE__" "__VERSION__" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
tcp_syn_stop \- eBPF TCP SYN flood protection daemon (BPF loader)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tcp_syn_stop
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBtcp_syn_stop\fR is a minimal BPF loader daemon that provides high-performance
TCP SYN flood protection using \fBeBPF (XDP and Tracepoints)\fR. It loads and
pins BPF programs, attaches XDP to network interfaces, monitors liveness,
and reloads whitelist/blacklist configuration on SIGHUP.

Policy logic (TTL expiry, autoban, intelligence persistence) is handled by
the companion \fBsyn-intel\fR service. Real-time visualization is provided by
\fBsyn-sight\fR.

The system uses a 3-tier defense architecture:
.IP 1. 4
\fBeBPF/XDP Layer\fR: Drops packets from blacklisted IPs and dynamically identified spoofed sources at wire speed.
Every drop is atomically counted per IP.
.IP 2. 4
\fBASN Auto-Ban\fR: \fBsyn-intel\fR automatically blocks entire subnet prefixes if multiple flagged IPs are identified from the same ASN.
.IP 3. 4
\fBnftables Layer\fR: Provides rate-limiting for non-spoofed senders and UDP flood protection.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-i ", " \-\-interface " INTERFACE"
Specify the network interface to attach the XDP program to. May be repeated
(max 8 interfaces). At least one interface is required.
.TP
.BI \-w ", " \-\-whitelist " FILE"
Path to the whitelist configuration file containing IPs or CIDR blocks that should never be blocked. Default is \fB/etc/tcp_syn_stop/whitelist.conf\fR.
.TP
.BI \-b ", " \-\-blacklist " FILE"
Path to the static blacklist configuration file. Default is \fB/etc/tcp_syn_stop/blacklist.conf\fR.
.TP
.BI \-l ", " \-\-logfile " FILE"
Path to a file where runtime logs should be written. If omitted, logs are sent to standard output (or syslog when running as a service).
.TP
.B \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose logging, including \fBlibbpf\fR debug output.
.TP
.B \-V ", " \-\-version
Print the program version and git revision, then exit.

.SH SIGNALS
.TP
.B SIGHUP
Reload whitelist and blacklist configuration files. Rate-limited to once
every 30 seconds.
.TP
.B SIGTERM, SIGINT
Gracefully shut down: unpin BPF maps, remove PID file, and exit.

.SH SECURITY
On startup, after attaching XDP and writing the PID file, the daemon drops
all capabilities except \fBCAP_BPF\fR and \fBCAP_NET_ADMIN\fR using
\fBlibcap\fR, and sets \fBPR_SET_NO_NEW_PRIVS\fR. The systemd unit file
provides additional sandboxing with \fBProtectSystem=full\fR,
\fBNoNewPrivileges\fR, \fBPrivateDevices\fR, \fBMemoryDenyWriteExecute\fR,
and kernel protection directives.

.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/tcp_syn_stop/whitelist.conf
Default whitelist configuration.
.TP
.I /etc/tcp_syn_stop/blacklist.conf
Default blacklist configuration.
.TP
.I /etc/tcp_syn_stop/tcp_syn_stop.conf
nftables ruleset for rate limiting and flood protection.
.TP
.I /sys/fs/bpf/tcp_syn_stop/
BPF maps pinned to bpffs. Used by \fBsyn-intel\fR and \fBsyn-sight\fR to
read and write map state.
.TP
.I /run/tcp_syn_stop/tcp_syn_stop.pid
PID file, used by \fBsyn-intel\fR to send SIGHUP on list changes.
.TP
.I /opt/tcp_syn_stop/ip2asn.db
SQLite database containing ASN mappings and attack intelligence records
(managed by \fBsyn-intel\fR).
.TP
.I /etc/logrotate.d/tcp_syn_stop
Log rotation policy for the daemon log file.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR nft (8),
.BR journalctl (1)

.SH AUTHOR
__MAINTAINER__
